# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers:
The structure has 8 distinct blocks and consists of 3 main layers:
- Bottom layer: 2 red arch blocks
- Middle layer: 1 yellow rectangular block with 2 cube blocks (green and blue) on top
- Top layer: 1 red arch block with an orange triangular roof

## Spatial Relationships:
- Bottom layer: Two red arch blocks (like bridges) positioned side by side as the foundation
- Middle layer: A yellow rectangular block positioned horizontally across the two red arch blocks
- Middle-top: A green cube positioned on the left side of the yellow block and a blue cube on the right side
- Top layer: A red arch block (with an opening) positioned on top of the structure, centered between the green and blue cubes
- Very top: An orange triangular roof piece sitting on top of the red arch block

# Selected Blocks from Dictionary

Based on my analysis, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:
1. Block with index 1 (red arch block, facing left)
2. Block with index 2 (red arch block, facing right)
3. Block with index 6 (red arch block with opening in front)
4. Block with index 7 (blue cube)
5. Block with index 8 (green cube)
6. Block with index 11 (yellow rectangular block, oriented horizontally)
7. Block with index 13 (orange triangular roof piece)

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 2
    Step3: Move block with index 11
    Step4: Move block with index 8
    Step5: Move block with index 7
    Step6: Move block with index 6
    Step7: Move block with index 13
}
```

This assembly sequence builds the structure from the ground up, starting with the foundation (red arch blocks), then adding the middle horizontal yellow block, followed by the green and blue cubes, then the top red arch block, and finally the orange triangular roof.
